{"questionId":"32941292","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the label will fit on the container.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>98589</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99294</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>≈</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0884</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong><br>the longest dimension of the label (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>) is less than both values and hence the label will fit (in any rotation) <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>R1<br></strong></em><br><strong>OR</strong><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Do not accept an argument based on the comparison of areas.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32941292","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.4f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the label will fit on the container.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}